The function should return the new vector after all threads have completed.

## Example usage:
```rust
fn main() {
    let mut words = vec!["apple", "banana", "pear", "peach"];
    pig_latinify(&mut words);
}
```
should yield the result `vec!["appleay", "ananabay", "earpay", "eachbay"]`.

## Constraints:
* Use only standard library functions.
* Do not use any external crates.
* You may write your own helper functions, but they should also only contain standard library code.
